No response. Do you wanna call it?

72
00:09:50,760 --> 00:09:53,228
Could be fine V-fib. Give me the paddles.

73
00:09:55,160 --> 00:09:57,116
Charge to 200.

74
00:09:57,240 --> 00:09:59,117
Charged to 200.

75
00:09:59,240 --> 00:10:00,719
<i>(man)</i> Clear.

76
00:10:11,720 --> 00:10:13,995
- 300.
- 300.

77
00:10:14,120 --> 00:10:16,236
Clear.

78
00:10:23,160 --> 00:10:25,390
360. Clear.

79
00:10:33,520 --> 00:10:35,750
- 360.
- 360.

80
00:10:35,880 --> 00:10:37,154
Clear.

81
00:10:55,840 --> 00:11:00,868
- <i>(woman #1)</i> We've got a sinus rhythm.
- <i>(woman #2)</i> Pressure's climbing.

82
00:11:01,000 --> 00:11:03,116
We're getting a response.

83
00:11:05,080 --> 00:11:08,197
It's OK. We brought you back.

84
00:11:08,840 --> 00:11:11,638
Check his oxygen saturation.

85
00:11:11,760 --> 00:11:15,070
<i>(woman)</i> Oxygen saturation is good.

86
00:11:15,200 --> 00:11:18,112
Blood pressure is 140 over 60.

87
00:11:34,280 --> 00:11:36,589
Hi. You're awake.

88
00:11:38,480 --> 00:11:42,075
I'm Sherry Clarke.
You're in Saint Elizabeth's ICU.

89
00:11:42,200 --> 00:11:45,829
- Are you my doctor?
- Better. I'm your nurse.

90
00:11:48,840 --> 00:11:51,195
The light hurts my eyes.

91
00:11:59,680 --> 00:12:02,877
- How long have I been here?
- A couple of days.

92
00:12:03,000 --> 00:12:08,757
Dr. Karras has been keeping an eye
on you. You're his latest project.

93
00:12:09,320 --> 00:12:11,914
Do you wanna watch some TV?

94
00:12:14,400 --> 00:12:16,868
- Anything in particular?
- No.

95
00:12:18,240 --> 00:12:22,995
Oh, dude, you lucked out.
This is my favorite movie of all time.

96
00:12:30,960 --> 00:12:32,837
<i>We belong dead.</i>

97
00:12:41,200 --> 00:12:43,156
<i>(static buzzes)</i>

98
00:13:12,360 --> 00:13:17,639
Hello, Abe. I'm Dr. Karras.
I'm just gonna have a little look.

99
00:13:18,760 --> 00:13:20,591
- Are you OK?
- I've been better.

100
00:13:20,720 --> 00:13:22,756
Remember why you're here?

101
00:13:22,880 --> 00:13:27,078
You were legally dead, but, lucky for you,
modern medicine knows no limits.

102
00:13:27,200 --> 00:13:31,751
- I died?
- Technically speaking. You had an NDE.

103
00:13:31,880 --> 00:13:34,997
- I don't know what that is.
- Near-death experience.

104
00:13:35,120 --> 00:13:39,875
It's my field of expertise. I fought to make
sure you were my patient. Let me guess.

105
00:13:40,000 --> 00:13:45,438
You saw a white light that engulfed you,
almost seemed to beckon you to stay.

106
00:13:45,560 --> 00:13:48,358
Yeah, that's exact...
How did you know that?

107
00:13:48,480 --> 00:13:53,554
As many as eight out of ten people who've
had an NDE report seeing a white light.

108
00:13:53,680 --> 00:13:56,513
- Freaky, huh?
- What about the light I'm seeing now?

109
00:13:56,640 --> 00:14:01,430
- It's probably an aura, a type of residue.
- So it's normal?

110
00:14:01,560 --> 00:14:05,269
I'd say we're well beyond
the bounds of normal here, but yes.

111
00:14:05,400 --> 00:14:11,350
You'll see 'em less frequently as time
passes and eventually they'll disappear.

112
00:14:32,480 --> 00:14:35,040
<i>(static buzzes)</i>

113
00:15:05,800 --> 00:15:07,631
<i>(crash)</i>

114
00:15:12,120 --> 00:15:14,076
<i>(clown music plays)</i>

115
00:15:24,480 --> 00:15:26,436
<i>(clown music)</i>

116
00:15:27,520 --> 00:15:30,114
<i>(music echoes and distorts)</i>

117
00:15:35,320 --> 00:15:38,710
<i>(static buzzes and crackles)</i>

118
00:15:45,720 --> 00:15:49,076
<i>(distorted electronic voices)</i>

119
00:15:51,400 --> 00:15:52,515
<i>(growling)</i>

120
00:15:59,920 --> 00:16:02,036
<i>(distorted electronic voices)</i>

121
00:16:02,160 --> 00:16:05,072
<i>(echoing voice) She's with us.</i>

122
00:16:05,200 --> 00:16:08,033
<i>She's with us.</i>

123
00:16:08,280 --> 00:16:11,272
<i>She's with us.</i>

124
00:16:15,960 --> 00:16:18,155
So everything looks fine.

125
00:16:19,360 --> 00:16:22,670
No masses, no deviations
in your intracranial space.

126
00:16:22,800 --> 00:16:25,553
But I've seen it three times
in the past few days.

127
00:16:25,680 --> 00:16:27,750
- Seen what?
- The white light.

128
00:16:27,880 --> 00:16:32,829
And there's something else.
You're gonna think I'm crazy, but, um...

129
00:16:33,600 --> 00:16:37,229
I'm seeing and hearing
all kinds of electrical stuff.

130
00:16:40,240 --> 00:16:42,595
EVP stands for
electronic voice phenomena.

131
00:16:42,720 --> 00:16:47,748
Precognition, the light you're seeing,
all that is part of supernatural white noise.

132
00:16:47,880 --> 00:16:51,429
- I've got a grant to study these things.
- So EVP, what exactly is it?

133
00:16:51,560 --> 00:16:56,839
It's the recording of the deceased using
a detuned apparatus like a TV or radio.

134
00:16:56,960 --> 00:17:00,635
Some people believe that EVP
is the afterlife manifest all around us.

135
00:17:00,760 --> 00:17:03,877
Others think it's a charge
or electromagnetic fields,

136
00:17:04,000 --> 00:17:08,596
still others that it's a means through
which the dead can communicate with us.

137
00:17:08,720 --> 00:17:12,110
Frankly, who knows? As long as
we're not exactly sure what it is,

138
00:17:12,240 --> 00:17:15,118
they'll keep funding my grant.

139
00:17:24,800 --> 00:17:27,234
What are you doing down here?

140
00:17:29,000 --> 00:17:32,151
This... is my EVP room.

141
00:17:32,640 --> 00:17:37,714
These have been detuned and I record 'em
to see if I've captured any transmissions.

142
00:17:37,840 --> 00:17:41,628
I suppose that's an important part
of your work, then?

143
00:17:41,760 --> 00:17:44,797
That? Oh.
No, I didn't want to detune that one.

144
00:17:44,920 --> 00:17:49,914
That's <i>Change of Habit</i>.
I'm recording it for research purposes.

145
00:17:50,040 --> 00:17:54,477
I thought I might learn something
from Dr. Presley.

146
00:17:54,960 --> 00:17:57,599
- You're not a fan of this one?
- No, it's just...

147
00:17:57,720 --> 00:18:00,837
I just saw one of those things
on the screen.

148
00:18:01,920 --> 00:18:05,276
Transmissions are only visible
after they've been recorded.

149
00:18:05,400 --> 00:18:07,595
On the last close-up of Elvis,

150
00:18:07,720 --> 00:18:13,033
I saw a blast of static with
what looked like an unformed person.

151
00:18:19,400 --> 00:18:24,110
- So what are you doing now?
- I've rewound the feed, I'll detune it.

152
00:18:24,240 --> 00:18:27,152
Let's see if you really saw something.

153
00:18:35,440 --> 00:18:38,557
There. There, that's it. That's it.

154
00:18:38,680 --> 00:18:41,911
That was it. That's what I saw.

155
00:18:45,320 --> 00:18:46,355
<i>(shrieking)</i>

156
00:18:46,920 --> 00:18:50,356
- I'll be damned.
- So what does that mean?

157
00:18:50,480 --> 00:18:55,270
Maybe when you had your NDE,
you yourself became a detuned receiver.

158
00:18:55,400 --> 00:19:01,350
You see white-noise transmissions, EVP,
communications with the dead, all that,

159
00:19:01,480 --> 00:19:03,436
without any of this.

160
00:19:04,440 --> 00:19:06,908
You're in uncharted territory.

161
00:19:07,040 --> 00:19:11,113
There's a very good chance you're
going to be seeing some wacky stuff.

162
00:19:13,840 --> 00:19:16,308
I've got to go.
I've got a doctor's appointment.

163
00:19:16,440 --> 00:19:20,319
Sure. Take all the time you need.
Hey, I'm still saving all the clippings

164
00:19:20,440 --> 00:19:22,874
and articles about the shooting and stuff.

165
00:19:23,000 --> 00:19:27,039
I don't want to hear about the day my wife
and son were brutally murdered, OK?

166
00:19:27,160 --> 00:19:30,072
I just can't handle that right now. I...

167
00:19:31,640 --> 00:19:32,675
I refuse.

168
00:19:37,080 --> 00:19:39,310
Hi. Dr. Karras asked...

169
00:19:40,080 --> 00:19:42,036
What's wrong?

170
00:19:42,160 --> 00:19:44,594
Dr. Karras is dead.

171
00:19:45,520 --> 00:19:48,830
- What?
- He had a heart attack early this morning.

172
00:19:56,200 --> 00:19:57,997
I'm sorry.

173
00:20:17,080 --> 00:20:19,878
- <i>(man)</i> OK, so this...
- EVP.

174
00:20:20,400 --> 00:20:22,470
EVP.

175
00:20:22,600 --> 00:20:25,194
It draws your attention to the white light.

176
00:20:25,320 --> 00:20:29,154
When you see the light, you think
it means... What do you think it means?

177
00:20:29,280 --> 00:20:33,751
That somebody's gonna die. Like with
Dr. Karras, it could be a couple of days.

178
00:20:33,880 --> 00:20:39,398
With the woman, it could be hours,
just depending on how strong the light is.

179
00:20:39,520 --> 00:20:44,275
I don't know, but I'm seeing it more and
it's driving me nuts. It's like being God.

180
00:20:44,400 --> 00:20:48,518
- I'm worried about you, Abe.
- Well, how would you explain it, then?

181
00:20:48,640 --> 00:20:51,200
How about, "I don't know"?

182
00:20:51,320 --> 00:20:55,393
In a city, we probably cross paths with
people who are about to die all the time.

183
00:20:55,520 --> 00:20:58,114
- We just don't know it.
- But what if I do, Marty?

184
00:20:58,240 --> 00:21:00,356
What if I do know
when somebody will die?

185
00:21:00,480 --> 00:21:04,758
- And now you've got this superpower?
- It's not a superpower.

186
00:21:05,360 --> 00:21:10,957
Call it what you want, but that sure as hell
sounds like superhero bullshit to me.

187
00:21:11,080 --> 00:21:13,275
Stop talking all this nonsense.

188
00:21:16,800 --> 00:21:18,756
<i>(static crackles)</i>

189
00:21:51,920 --> 00:21:54,195
<i>(car horn blares)</i>

190
00:21:58,840 --> 00:22:01,559
<i>(echoing whispers)</i>

191
