Come on, you stupid thing.

194
00:22:56,080 --> 00:22:58,036
Get over the track.

195
00:23:03,160 --> 00:23:07,153
- Oh, you've got to be kidding me.
- Come on!

196
00:23:07,280 --> 00:23:09,430
Hey!

197
00:23:09,560 --> 00:23:11,596
You've gotta move!

198
00:23:11,720 --> 00:23:12,948
<i>(train whistle)</i>

199
00:23:13,600 --> 00:23:15,477
Come on!

200
00:23:15,600 --> 00:23:17,750
Get out of there!

201
00:23:26,160 --> 00:23:27,309
Move!

202
00:23:32,320 --> 00:23:33,355
Hey!

203
00:23:34,720 --> 00:23:39,157
- Get outta there!
- I can't! My foot's caught! Help me!

204
00:23:41,120 --> 00:23:43,076
Help me!

205
00:23:43,200 --> 00:23:45,509
Get off the track!

206
00:23:49,160 --> 00:23:50,957
Move!

207
00:24:27,880 --> 00:24:30,394
<i>(echoing) I'm so sorry.</i>

208
00:24:55,880 --> 00:24:58,030
<i>(distorted voice echoes)</i>

209
00:25:18,280 --> 00:25:20,555
<i>(voice continues)</i>

210
00:26:01,000 --> 00:26:03,309
<i>(clattering)</i>

211
00:26:22,600 --> 00:26:25,512
<i>(rattling)</i>

212
00:26:37,000 --> 00:26:39,036
<i>(faint voices)</i>

213
00:27:06,960 --> 00:27:09,110
<i>(echoing voices whisper)</i>

214
00:27:12,720 --> 00:27:14,472
<i>(voices fade)</i>

215
00:27:34,120 --> 00:27:38,193
- <i>(Marty) Yeah?</i>
- How'd you feel about me dropping by?

216
00:27:38,320 --> 00:27:41,471
<i>Abe, uh...</i>
<i>Yeah, sure. When?</i>

217
00:27:41,600 --> 00:27:44,160
How does right freaking now grab you?

218
00:27:44,280 --> 00:27:46,236
Thanks.

219
00:27:50,720 --> 00:27:53,598
<i>(static crackles)</i>

220
00:27:53,720 --> 00:27:55,711
What the...?

221
00:27:57,840 --> 00:27:59,956
No way.

222
00:28:03,720 --> 00:28:05,790
<i>(man)</i> Son of a bitch.

223
00:28:19,920 --> 00:28:21,990
Excuse me, sir

224
00:28:22,800 --> 00:28:24,631
- Dammit.
- You should get out.

225
00:28:24,760 --> 00:28:29,231
Beat it, kid. I've dropped a couple
of lug nuts. I think I can handle it.

226
00:28:33,720 --> 00:28:35,870
I don't think that bumper is gonna hold.

227
00:28:36,000 --> 00:28:39,879
Look, I don't need some dipshit kid
telling me what to do, OK?

228
00:28:40,000 --> 00:28:45,438
So you can take your metrosexual ass
back to your yuppie car and...

229
00:28:46,520 --> 00:28:48,078
- Whoa!
- What are you doing?

230
00:28:48,200 --> 00:28:51,351
- The bumper was gonna...
- Get away from me.

231
00:29:09,560 --> 00:29:12,438
I owe you my life.

232
00:29:28,120 --> 00:29:31,192
No, Marty, I swear to God, I am fine.

233
00:29:31,320 --> 00:29:33,914
<i>All right. All right, but maybe you should...</i>

234
00:29:34,040 --> 00:29:37,191
<i>I don't know, take a little time off</i>
<i>or something, you know.</i>

