You bitch!

299
00:38:13,240 --> 00:38:16,437
Hey. Hey, are you OK?

300
00:38:16,560 --> 00:38:18,152
Yeah.

301
00:38:18,400 --> 00:38:20,516
Yeah.

302
00:38:20,640 --> 00:38:23,677
I think you just saved my life.

303
00:38:25,560 --> 00:38:31,157
Well, it's beginning to be a fucking habit.
Trust me, it's no big deal.

304
00:38:31,280 --> 00:38:35,796
- Dude, it was my life.
- Well, I didn't mean it like that.

305
00:38:37,040 --> 00:38:39,508
It's you.

306
00:38:39,640 --> 00:38:42,473
Yeah. Yeah, you were my nurse.

307
00:38:53,160 --> 00:38:55,754
It's busted.

308
00:38:57,400 --> 00:38:59,789
I'm so sorry.

309
00:39:02,120 --> 00:39:04,270
That's OK.

310
00:39:04,400 --> 00:39:06,391
- You're hurt. Let me look.
- It's fine.

311
00:39:06,520 --> 00:39:08,476
Hey.

312
00:39:09,920 --> 00:39:13,629
Let me fix you up.
It's the least I can do. Come on.

313
00:39:15,240 --> 00:39:20,712
It's a superficial laceration. Nothing a few
stitches and antibiotics can't take care of.

314
00:39:20,840 --> 00:39:25,789
You are either staring at my ring
or admiring my rack. Which is it?

315
00:39:25,920 --> 00:39:29,390
- The ring. I was...
- I'm just kidding.

316
00:39:30,320 --> 00:39:33,517
It's my old wedding ring.
My husband died a couple of years ago

317
00:39:33,640 --> 00:39:36,916
so I like to keep it close to my heart.

318
00:39:38,040 --> 00:39:40,759
You must have loved him very much.

319
00:39:41,800 --> 00:39:43,074
Yeah.

320
00:39:44,160 --> 00:39:48,597
He was a music teacher
at Sacred Heart Elementary,

321
00:39:48,720 --> 00:39:51,075
and those kids adored him.

322
00:39:51,200 --> 00:39:55,671
He had a unique approach. No doh-ray-mi
crap. He'd organize this recital every year,

323
00:39:55,800 --> 00:39:59,873
have the kids sing Bowie, Pink Floyd,
Rush, The Beach Boys, Jane's Addiction.

324
00:40:00,000 --> 00:40:04,073
- You name it.
- Sounds amazing.

325
00:40:04,200 --> 00:40:07,636
Yeah. It was incredible.

326
00:40:07,760 --> 00:40:11,833
But the end just... It came so quick.

327
00:40:13,280 --> 00:40:16,556
One day we're just living, you know?

328
00:40:17,200 --> 00:40:20,829
Then, boom, he's dead.

329
00:40:21,840 --> 00:40:24,195
That's terrible.

330
00:40:24,320 --> 00:40:26,072
Yeah.

331
00:40:27,080 --> 00:40:29,196
But...

332
00:40:29,320 --> 00:40:31,629
I wake up

333
00:40:31,760 --> 00:40:33,751
and it just hit me.

334
00:40:33,880 --> 00:40:37,395
I had to let Tommy go.

335
00:40:38,280 --> 00:40:41,750
I'll see him again someday. Until then,

336
00:40:41,880 --> 00:40:45,031
you have to accept
what it's supposed to be about.

337
00:40:49,640 --> 00:40:52,632
- Did you two have any kids?
- No.

338
00:40:52,760 --> 00:40:56,309
No. But I still put on the recital
every year in his honor.

339
00:40:56,440 --> 00:40:58,795
The next one's in a couple of days.

340
00:41:00,360 --> 00:41:03,875
- And you should totally come.
- Maybe.

341
00:41:06,760 --> 00:41:09,479
Here.

342
00:41:11,120 --> 00:41:13,680
Take this. Think it over.

343
00:41:13,800 --> 00:41:16,553
Call me if you're interested.

344
00:41:17,040 --> 00:41:19,508
Hey, the cops are here.

345
00:41:19,640 --> 00:41:22,552
Yeah. Tell them their timing sucks.

346
00:41:45,000 --> 00:41:49,198
<i>(Danny) Is this the present you got Dad</i>
<i>for your anniversary? Can I see it? Can I?</i>

347
00:41:49,320 --> 00:41:51,959
<i>I don't suppose your dad</i>
<i>put you up to this, did he?</i>

348
00:41:52,080 --> 00:41:56,278
<i>(Danny) No way. Just wondering is all.</i>
<i>I bet it's that watch he wanted, right?</i>

349
00:41:56,400 --> 00:41:59,039
<i>You tell your dad</i>
<i>that he's just gonna have to wait.</i>

350
00:41:59,160 --> 00:42:01,469
<i>Besides, it's just a few days away.</i>

351
00:42:03,960 --> 00:42:05,473
<i>(bus horn blares)</i>

352
00:42:07,000 --> 00:42:10,834
- <i>Are you all right?</i>
- <i>I'm OK, Mom. That man saved our lives.</i>

353
00:42:10,960 --> 00:42:13,633
<i>Thank you!</i>

354
00:42:13,760 --> 00:42:16,479
<i>That's all right.</i>

355
00:42:31,400 --> 00:42:33,630
<i>That's all right.</i>

356
00:43:17,560 --> 00:43:19,278
Henry Caine.

357
00:43:19,400 --> 00:43:21,834
<i>(electronic whine)</i>

358
00:43:25,280 --> 00:43:27,669
<i>(electronic screech)</i>

359
00:44:05,000 --> 00:44:09,039
<i>(echoing electronic voice) Should not</i>
<i>have saved. Should not have saved.</i>

360
00:44:09,160 --> 00:44:13,278
<i>Should not have saved.</i>
<i>Should not have saved.</i>

361
00:44:13,400 --> 00:44:16,710
<i>(woman whispers) Should not...</i>

362
00:44:16,840 --> 00:44:20,355
<i>have saved.</i>

363
00:45:04,760 --> 00:45:08,992
- Julia Caine? My name is Abraham...
- Abraham Dale.

364
00:45:09,120 --> 00:45:12,237
I always knew you'd come.
Please, come on in.

365
00:45:12,360 --> 00:45:15,272
Excuse the mess. We're moving.

366
00:45:36,680 --> 00:45:40,355
I am so sorry for what my husband did
to your wife and son.

367
00:45:40,480 --> 00:45:45,838
Henry was the most down-to-earth, don't-
question-things guy you could ever meet.

368
00:45:45,960 --> 00:45:47,996
So, uh...

369
00:45:49,800 --> 00:45:52,234
so what happened, then?

370
00:45:52,360 --> 00:45:54,874
He, uh...

371
00:45:55,000 --> 00:45:57,355
he had a near-death experience.

372
00:45:58,560 --> 00:46:00,790
He was hit by a drunk driver head-on.

373
00:46:00,920 --> 00:46:05,311
He must have died three times that night.
They finally revived him in the early hours

374
00:46:05,440 --> 00:46:08,796
and then we brought him home
a week later.

375
00:46:08,920 --> 00:46:10,876
That's when it all began -

376
00:46:11,000 --> 00:46:15,869
the strange behavior,
the weird ideas about life, about death.

377
00:46:16,000 --> 00:46:18,639
He just got so obsessed
with the paranormal.

378
00:46:18,760 --> 00:46:23,993
EVP, the white light,
precognition, all that kind of stuff.

379
00:46:24,120 --> 00:46:27,237
He even thought he could save people.

380
00:46:28,320 --> 00:46:31,756
At first I thought it was understandable.
This man almost died.

381
00:46:31,880 --> 00:46:35,839
But then it just got to be too much.

382
00:46:35,960 --> 00:46:37,951
What do you mean by too much?

383
00:46:42,280 --> 00:46:44,919
I'll show you.

384
00:47:07,160 --> 00:47:09,913
You see? I'll leave you to it.

385
00:50:02,160 --> 00:50:04,879
Oh, shit!

386
00:50:11,440 --> 00:50:13,237
<i>(screeching)</i>

387
00:50:17,760 --> 00:50:19,955
<i>(echoing voices)</i>

388
00:50:31,280 --> 00:50:34,078
Henry was always blowing fuses in here.

389
00:50:34,200 --> 00:50:37,033
Really? Hm.

390
00:50:37,160 --> 00:50:38,991
Um...

391
00:50:40,160 --> 00:50:43,470
Do you have any idea
what the e stands for?

392
00:50:43,600 --> 00:50:44,715
No.

393
00:50:46,160 --> 00:50:49,197
Would you mind if I took
some of this stuff to look over?

394
00:50:49,320 --> 00:50:51,675
Sure. I don't want any of it.

395
00:50:53,040 --> 00:50:56,999
Look, I am sorry again
for what my husband did.

396
00:50:57,120 --> 00:50:59,918
I can't believe how far gone he is.

397
00:51:00,040 --> 00:51:03,396
- "Is"? What are you talking about?
- What do you mean?

398
00:51:03,520 --> 00:51:06,512
- You said "is".
- And?

399
00:51:06,640 --> 00:51:10,030
Don't you mean "was"?
"How far gone he was"?

400
00:51:10,160 --> 00:51:12,116
You don't know?

401
00:51:16,200 --> 00:51:21,115
- <i>(Julia) Henry's still alive.</i>
- <i>(Abe) I saw him pull the trigger.</i>

402
00:51:21,240 --> 00:51:24,118
<i>(Julia) He survived.</i>
<i>He's over at Belmont County.</i>

403
00:51:24,240 --> 00:51:26,196
<i>(Abe) The asylum.</i>

404
00:51:36,360 --> 00:51:39,238
We keep him up here.
He's been with us a couple of months,

405
00:51:39,360 --> 00:51:41,749
since he slipped out of coma land.

406
00:51:41,880 --> 00:51:44,838
If you ask me,
he ain't never gonna see a courtroom.

407
00:51:44,960 --> 00:51:46,188
Why?

408
00:51:46,320 --> 00:51:48,993
Old Henry...

409
00:51:49,120 --> 00:51:51,634
he sees dead people.

410
00:52:01,640 --> 00:52:07,590
Don't mind me. I'm just gonna stick
around and make sure you boys play nice.

411
00:52:12,000 --> 00:52:14,355
My wife and my son.

412
00:52:16,600 --> 00:52:18,830
Why did you do it?

413
00:52:18,960 --> 00:52:21,793
Why did you kill them?

414
00:52:23,920 --> 00:52:27,117
If save, must kill.

415
00:52:28,360 --> 00:52:31,238
Jesus, you're even crazier
than I thought you'd be.

416
00:52:31,360 --> 00:52:33,316
If save,

417
00:52:34,360 --> 00:52:36,954
responsible.

418
00:52:37,080 --> 00:52:39,674
Responsible for what?

419
00:52:40,680 --> 00:52:43,114
Consequences.

420
00:52:43,240 --> 00:52:45,470
Horrific consequences.

421
00:52:45,960 --> 00:52:47,951
What consequences?

422
00:53:08,960 --> 00:53:12,669
It will never end if you let him in.

423
00:53:15,920 --> 00:53:19,390
You cannot shut the dead out.

424
00:53:19,520 --> 00:53:23,672
The dead will haunt you
until you put right what you've done.

425
00:53:24,320 --> 00:53:27,039
If you save, you must...

426
00:53:27,160 --> 00:53:29,674
you must kill.

427
00:53:30,840 --> 00:53:33,229
<i>Tria Mera.</i>

428
00:53:35,600 --> 00:53:37,318
<i>Tria Mera.</i>

429
00:53:38,520 --> 00:53:41,193
- Trio what?
- <i>Tria Mera!</i>

430
00:53:51,640 --> 00:53:52,959
<i>(alarm bell)</i>

431
00:53:55,760 --> 00:53:57,796
If save, must kill.

432
00:54:15,040 --> 00:54:17,873
If save, must kill.

433
00:54:18,120 --> 00:54:22,716
If save, must kill. If save, must kill!

434
00:55:25,200 --> 00:55:27,953
It's a three.

435
00:55:28,080 --> 00:55:32,198
What does a three
have to do with the devil's signature?

436
00:55:32,320 --> 00:55:34,276
<i>(knock at door)</i>

437
00:55:42,960 --> 00:55:45,269
- Hi, Abe.
- Hi.

438
00:55:45,400 --> 00:55:49,996
So I just finished the rehearsals for
that recital thingy I was telling you about,

439
00:55:50,120 --> 00:55:53,430
so I was basically in the neighborhood,

440
00:55:53,560 --> 00:55:54,788
and, uh...

441
00:55:54,920 --> 00:55:57,115
Hi.

442
00:55:57,240 --> 00:56:00,835
- I hope you don't mind that I stopped by.
- No, no. I don't...

443
00:56:00,960 --> 00:56:02,916
I don't mind. Um...

444
00:56:03,960 --> 00:56:06,394
But why?

445
00:56:06,520 --> 00:56:08,476
When...

446
00:56:09,640 --> 00:56:12,108
is the last time you drank
a cheap bottle of wine?

447
00:56:12,240 --> 00:56:15,357
That's very kind,
but you really don't have to do that.

448
00:56:15,480 --> 00:56:17,630
I know I don't have to.

449
00:56:17,760 --> 00:56:19,671
I want to.

450
00:56:19,800 --> 00:56:21,631
I'm married.

451
00:56:23,600 --> 00:56:26,034
But thank you.

452
00:56:27,680 --> 00:56:30,672
Abe, I read your file.

453
00:56:31,360 --> 00:56:33,828
I know why you were in the ICU
when we first met.

454
00:56:33,960 --> 00:56:37,430
I know what happened
to Rebecca and Danny.

455
00:56:38,320 --> 00:56:41,198
You saved my life the other night.

456
00:56:41,760 --> 00:56:44,433
I'd love to return the favor.

457
00:56:53,440 --> 00:56:56,113
<i>(echoing voices whisper)</i>

458
00:57:27,160 --> 00:57:30,516
- <i>(Abe)</i> I like the hair color.
- <i>(Sherry)</i> Purple was good, but...

459
00:57:30,640 --> 00:57:33,871
- <i>(Abe)</i> It goes with the wine.
- Right.

460
00:57:34,000 --> 00:57:36,309
This is great. It really is.

461
00:57:36,440 --> 00:57:38,635
Thank you very much.

462
00:57:39,680 --> 00:57:42,672
- To bad wine and good company.
- Oh, it's bad.

463
00:57:47,880 --> 00:57:50,314
You gotta get out
and do stuff like this, though.

464
00:57:50,440 --> 00:57:53,398
It's the only way you'll make it through.

465
00:57:57,840 --> 00:58:00,832
Danny and Rebecca were my everything.

466
00:58:02,360 --> 00:58:04,635
And Tommy was mine.

467
00:58:05,840 --> 00:58:08,513
But you can't just throw in the towel, Abe.

468
00:58:20,360 --> 00:58:22,669
- Come on.
- Where are we going?

469
00:58:22,800 --> 00:58:24,233
O'Malley's.

470
00:58:24,360 --> 00:58:28,956
I gotta kick your ass in a game of pool
